  "prompt": "Which raw materials are needed for photosynthesis?",
  "response": "Photosynthesis requires three main raw materials:\n\n1. **Carbon Dioxide (CO\u2082)**: This gas is absorbed from the atmosphere through small openings in plant leaves called stomata.\n\n2. **Water (H\u2082O)**: Water is absorbed from the soil through the plant roots.\n\n3. **Sunlight**: This provides the energy necessary for the photosynthesis process. Plants capture sunlight using a pigment called chlorophyll, which is primarily found in the leaves.\n\nThese raw materials are used by plants to produce glucose and oxygen in the process of photosynthesis. The general equation for photosynthesis is:\n\n\\[ \\text{6 CO}_2 + \\text{6 H}_2\\text{O} + \\text{light energy} \\rightarrow \\text{C}_6\\text{H}_{12}\\text{O}_6 + \\text{6 O}_2 \\]\n\nIn this equation, carbon dioxide and water, in the presence of light energy, produce glucose (C\u2086H\u2081\u2082O\u2086) and oxygen (O\u2082).",
